Date: Sun, 31 Dec 2023 05:03:33 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: b43: Stop/wake correct queue in DMA Tx path when QoS is disabled
Git-commit: 9636951e4468f02c72cc75a82dc65d003077edbc
Patch-mainline: v6.9-rc1
References: git-fixes bsc#1222961 CVE-2023-52644

When QoS is disabled, the queue priority value will not map to the correct
ieee80211 queue since there is only one queue. Stop/wake queue 0 when QoS
is disabled to prevent trying to stop/wake a non-existent queue and failing
to stop/wake the actual queue instantiated.

